subSubSection.paragraph:
Delopleurus pullus
Boheman 1857

; 
Péringuey 1901
; 
Ferreira 1972
; 
Gillet 1911
; 
Janssens 1939
.

Beetles are small (
4.5–6.1 mm
), strongly convex, black or dark brown, upper surface glabrous.

Pygidium with relatively slender borders and convex disc. Basal border slender and almost parallel-sided except in the middle. Apical border about twice as thick in the middle as the basal border, becoming more slender laterally. Disc glabrous, punctate with punctures separated by one to two puncture diameters (
Figure 3B
).

Parameres with a small protrusion ventroapically (visible in lateral view, 
Figure 3C
).

Female
(
Figure 3D
) can be separated from male in having acute, not bifurcated spurs of anterior tibiae and disc of pygidium with small granules and setae (
Figure 3E
).

The species is widely distributed in the northern part of Southern Africa (
Figure 3F
).
